review_460228910~“Great Hotel”~Perfect location. Right size hotel to keep the personal touch but provide all the services you need. Great staff . Have not tried the restaurant yet but look forward to that when the opportunity arises ~5~5~5~5~5~5~5~nan
review_459008514~“Good value”~New hotel, small rooms but nice, handy location to Valley or $13 taxi to Queen St, good onsite carpark, quiet street, some rooms affected by adjoining building aircon noise -suggest rooms 3 to 7 and 14 to 19 on levels 3 or 4, good food at their adjoining restaurant, nice staff.~4~5~4~4~4~5~5~nan
review_458793057~“Great hotel!”~Great hotel, great service. The staff were amazing. The food was excellent and the rooms were very clean and comfortable. The location is very central to all of the CBDemocratic with easy access to motorways if going north or south plus the hotel has great parking and not expensive. I loved it.  Will definitely be back!~5~5~5~5~5~5~5~nan
review_458447873~“Much to improve.”~The hotel is a 20 minute walk away from CBD, is modern with great design features & the reception team were super friendly both on check in & when I had problems. Unfortunately however the 5 night stay was far from great - the cleaning was neglected 2 of the 5 nights & throughout the stay I had to ask reception for tea & toiletries as they hadn't replaced them. The bed was comfortable but the sheets & towels had a strange odour and I was woken up very early as the curtain doesn't fully close. I expect all hotels to have black out curtain / blinds, but this was a huge problem for me breaking up my sleep cycle. There is alot of potential here, just some work needs to be done to make this a much smoother experience.~3~3~4~2~3~2~3~nan
review_458187918~“Mantra Richmont Hotel”~Very slow to check in with issues which then had to be resolved at check out. Bathroom glass was unclean (words legible in the steam. The television remote would not turn on the TV. Room was clean and the bed was great (slept very well).~3~4~4~4~3~3~2~nan
review_457779611~“Good value for room”~Rooms were fresh and new. Very clean. Great bed. Room was a little small but was ok, it suited our purpose. We would definitely stay here again. Aircon was cool. Linens were New, clean and white. Good value for price.~5~5~5~5~5~5~5~nan
review_457526515~“Welcoming and nice”~Good location, welcoming reception, very nice modern room and super comfy bed. Brooke the reception lady was cheerful and went out of her way to help me post an over-sized parcel because it was Sunday and I couldn't.  The only negative feedback about our stay was the questionably hot and stuffy floor we arrived at and upon entering the room. It was about as hot as the 30 degree day outside. Took a few minutes for the air-conditioning to kick in for relieve. Other than this, it is a nice place that's close to Fortitude Valley and very comfortable. I would still return the next time I visit.~4~4~3~4~3~4~4~nan
review_457460117~“Very convenient and quiet.”~Close to the CBD, yet far enough to not have to deal with the hustle and bustle of the CBD. Perfect location. Chinatown and the night clubs are a short stroll away from the hotel. Hotel rooms are clean and spacious. I love the rain shower, the shower gels and shampoos provided. Staff at the front desk are very friendly and helpful when it comes to making your stay comfortable.~4~5~5~5~5~5~5~nan
review_457455369~“Great location”~Totally shocked by the value of this motel, the room is on the small but didn't bother me as it was clean and comfy. I recieved a extra bonus with breakfast included great food and service. Motel was walking distance to the Valley had a great time.~5~5~5~5~5~5~5~nan
review_457451082~“Business Stay”~I enjoyed the 2 day stay while on business in Brisbane. Great reception staff, great food, great shower! bed was comfy, location was great, short walk to the Valley. I would recommend to anyone. Only cons were max 25 deg a little too cold for me, and pillows too high. Everything else was great.~4~5~4~3~5~4~5~nan
